{"id": "duc04-testb-20:6#19", "contents": "Jiang's speech emphasized the importance of stability over the next year, citing two key events on the political calendar: the 50th anniversary of Communist Party rule on October 1 and China's recovery of the Portuguese colony of Macau on December 20. He noted that officials must be strengthened in their ideological and political education to resist hostile domestic and foreign forces. Jiang likened the threat of political enemies to that of white-collar and ordinary criminals, highlighting potentially volatile problems such as inefficient state industries, laid-off workers, and corrupt officials."}
